A Man ( Greek : Ενας Ανδρας , transliteration : Enas Andras , Italian : Un Uomo ) is a novel written by Orianna Fallaci chronicling her relationship with the attempted assassin of Greek dictator George Papadopoulos . The book is a sort of biography written about Alexandros Panagoulis written in the form of a novel . Fallaci had an intense romantic relationship with Panagoulis . She uses the novel to put forth her views that Panagoulis was assassinated by a vasy conspiracy , a view widely shared by many Greeks . It allows us to live , my boy . A man who gives in does n't live , he survives. " . 